 style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bot=
tom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Develop significant in-house capabilities acros=
s their stack.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-=
sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Modularize commoditiz=
ed components while controlling overall system integration.</p></li><li sty=
le=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb=
(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom:=
 0; padding-left: 4px;">Compete directly with incumbents.</p></li><li style=
=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0=
; padding-left: 4px;">Offer products that are better, faster, or cheaper (o=
ften all three).</p></li></ol><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">For Vertical Integrators, t=
he integration is the innovation.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 5=
5); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Let&#8217;s go=
 back to the Base example to unpack that. Battery pack assembly is one of t=
he many activities the company does. As I wrote in the piece:&#160;</p><blo=
ckquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #0c2427; margin: 20px 0; padding: 0=
;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>To deploy batteries and f=
ix the grid, Base can&#8217;t just build a battery; it needs to build a ver=
tically integrated power </span><strong>company</strong><span> around batte=
ries.&#160;</span></em></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em>The pow=
er company needs to excel at a whole lot of things: manufacturing, finance,=
 distributed systems, power trading, customer acquisition, consumer softwar=
e, regulatory, and installation, to start. It needs to become a Retail Elec=
tric Provider (REP) itself.</em></p></blockquote><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Ea=
ch of those things is hard but achievable. What&#8217;s novel is their comb=
ination into one coherent product. I recommend </span><a href=3D"https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/4054d256-0fa9-43f3-a64e-09aacbabf96e?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(5=
4, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">reading the Deep Dive</a><span> to=
 understand how the company has thought about fitting them together. Each p=
ermutation comes with trade-offs: &#8220;Move one thing here, and something=
 else changes there. Move </span><em>that</em><span> and something </span><=
em>else </em><span>shifts.&#8221;&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54=
, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">The dec=
ision to manufacture packs but not cells is one of many such decisions, and=
 it highlights the difference between &#8220;deep tech&#8221; companies and=
 Vertical Integrators. Let me explain.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, =
55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Battery c=
ells are the basic unit of the battery, the place where the chemistry that =
stores and discharges electricity happens. There are a number of large comp=
anies, startups, and research labs working on improving the performance of =
the current most popular chemistry, lithium-ion, and on developing new chem=
istries altogether.&#160;</p><div class=3D"captioned-image-container-static=
